        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 2:57PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Veterans Park, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lexington, Veterans Park, Cadentown, Fayette Mall, Chilesburg,
Spears, Coletown, Valley View, Athens, and Logana.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
